  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated a willingness to make restitution by partially repaying the funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the shout from the gallery regarding a 10-year sentence is an emotional outburst that bears no relation to sentencing guidelines, which typically favor rehabilitation and restorative justice for first-time, non-violent economic offenses involving this amount of money. A sentence of 8 months is sufficient to address the criminality of the act while considering the defendant's lack of a prior record and ongoing repayment efforts.",
  "verdict": 8
}
